entries.femaleVariant: Ahh… Been a damned long while, old friend.
entries.maleVariant: Heh… Been a damned long while, old friend.

entries.femaleVariant: Let's see what we got here…
entries.maleVariant: Hm. Let's see what we got here…

entries.femaleVariant: Hey! What the--? Hands off my car!
It broke down.
Not your business!
'Cause it broke down and I--
Not your biz.
And you abandoned it and now, outta nowhere, you remembered you'd left it? Likely story.
Not my biz?!
This last week, I've put in sweat, smarts... anything to get this heap running!
Almost hate to admit it, but good work.
You're a piss poor mechanic, then.
All in all… did a pretty good job. Here I thought the car was done for, gone, but… ehh.
entries.maleVariant: All in all… did a pretty good job. Here I thought the car was done for, gone, but… huh.

entries.femaleVariant: Took a week? Pff. Piss poor mechanic, then. I'da brought it back to life in a day if I'd set my heart on it.
But you didn't. Missed your chance, now.
Hahaha! Ah, like clockwork!
Must not've wanted it… cared as much as I do.
Buy the car off you.
They're my wheels. That's that.
You can keep the car.
I'll buy this car off you. Pay you enough so you can get another.
But... i-t's a wreck…
Had enough of this convo. You ghost – now.
Mhm. My damn wreck. C'mon, take the cash before I change my mind.
entries.maleVariant: Uh-huh. My damn wreck. C'mon, take the cash before I change my mind.

entries.femaleVariant: Timing chain's about rusted through.
So?
You'll wanna replace it, else it's liable to snap if you open her up even a bit, take her over thirty.
Hold on, hold on… Mean to say I can have her?
Well, definitely no guy or girl magnet... but seems healthy under the hood.
Don't know the half of it. Wait till I open 'er up.
Not afraid you might--? Ahh, what can it hurt. I'm dead anyway.
Well, well... This nomad planted roots? Could it be?
Dunno. Hard to ruminate on that when you got a fuckin' time-bomb lodged in your head.
New coil, plugs... Hm, an' somebody's clearly been tinkerin' with the camshaft. What's this, now?
entries.maleVariant: New coil, plugs... Somebody's clearly been tinkerin' with the camshaft. What's this, now?

entries.femaleVariant: Thi--? Wha--? N-no! It's my car!
entries.maleVariant: Thi--? Wha--? No! It's my car!

entries.femaleVariant: No! Why would you leave it rusting in a yard?!
Don't get it, do you. Car's a sacred thing to a nomad. You tinkering with it? It's like you dug up one of my loved one's graves.
Fuck your philosophy of life. I don't care. You're not gettin' the car back. It's that simple!
I need this car. To leave the city. Leave it and never come back.
Why's that?
'Cause... 'cause it's my ticket outta this fuckin' city. My only way out.
Why you so desperate to leave?
Seem desperate. Why you wanna leave?
No way you'd understand if you have to ask.
C'mon, try me, tell me.
Tell you what, dammit? Look around you. Dirt, rot, shit and scum…
Jeez... thanks... Not sure what to say.
So give it a think… while I take this baby for a ride.
I told you clearly that--
Need me to pull heat on you? Really want that? Step away from the car. Do it, now.
Fuck you! Fuck you sideways, you cunt!
entries.maleVariant: Fuck you! Fuck you sideways, asshole!

entries.femaleVariant: Thanks for the fixes. Clever girl.
Mean to say ya can. Wouldn't have a use for her here anyway. Not your typical urban vehicle.
Roads rise to meet you, clever girl.
I don't wanna live here. Not now.
Hate to sound like your conscience, wouldn't ever want that job… but dick move, V.
Not a nomad, no way you can understand. It's as if somebody klepped your guitar.
Mhm. Somebody for who it was the last chance for a better life?
Enjoy your fuckin' ride, V.
Floor it, V.
If it's any consolation, fuckin' time-bomb feels shitty about it, too.
I know, Johnny. C'mon, let's ghost. This place makes my skin crawl.
Shoulda started with the step motor.
Shoulda started with the step motor. Woulda been quicker.
Says who? And why?
Cause it's iffy, starts stickin'. But clear the carbon deposits and it starts runnin' like new again.
Fuuuck… I replaced the entire throttle…
Ah, see? Takes the owner to really know a set of wheels.
Former owner. Car's mine now. Soon as I'm done doin' the basic fixes, I am leavin' this fuckin' city in a cloud of exhaust.
[Lift hood]
[Examine engine]
It's warm. Engine was runnin' just a short while ago.
Fenders and trunk eaten away by rust... rest of the body's still holdin' up. Wonder what's under the hood...
[Check radiator]
[Drop hood] What? This car's mine!
[Check oil pan]
Someone cleaned the cooling fan and filled up the brake fluid... except... huh... with water.
entries.maleVariant: Someone cleaned the cooling fan, filled up the brake fluid... except... huh... with water.

entries.femaleVariant: Haha. New, but used. Salvaged from some other junker.
entries.maleVariant: Huh. New, but used. Salvaged from some other junker.

entries.femaleVariant: All right. Seen enough.
